  "body": "In the [mutan example](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/wiki/Mutan-0.2-Example#life-insurance) line `if this.data[0] == \"heartbeat\" {`, the \"heartbeat\" string is converted by mutan to a left-padded hex value. However, if the data argument is prepared in javascript like this:\n`var data = \"heartbeat\".pad(32).unbin();`\nthe value sent with the transaction is right-padded, causing the mutan `if` conditional (opcode EQ in the debugger) to fail. A simple fix is to prepare a string data argument like this:\n`var data = \"heartbeat\".pad(32,0).unbin();`\nIs [String.pad()](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/develop/ethereal/assets/ext/string.js#L2-L6) acting correctly when the 2nd argument is missing?\n",
